                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T07:11:04.944106Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: After meticulously creating a typed daily routine and feeding schedule for her infant daughter, Priya returned from work to find the nanny had improvised the meals and skipped the structured nap window entirely, citing the baby's mood. \u2014 The experience deepened her control-versus-delegation tension, making her reluctant to outsource decisions involving her child's wellbeing and driving her to systematize household protocols in exhaustive detail.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T07:11:04.944106Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "2da1b625-3036-46e4-bd07-30b8da193754",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T07:11:04.944118Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: When researching air purifiers before her daughter's birth, Priya ignored two expert blog recommendations after a trusted colleague's mothers' group shared consistent, specific complaints about the same models' filter replacement costs. \u2014 This confirmed her primary trust orientation toward peers over institutions or advertising, and she now systematically consults known-network reviews before any significant household or family purchase.",
