          },
          {
            "title": "First Salary Budget Reckoning",
            "when": "age 25",
            "event": "Three months into his first full-time analytics role at a Chennai-based firm, Arjun built a detailed spreadsheet tracking every expense and realized his salary left almost no margin after rent, food, and student loan repayments in a metro city.",
            "lasting_impact": "The stark numbers made risk feel viscerally dangerous, reinforcing his low risk tolerance and creating a persistent internal tension between wanting quality products and staying within tight financial constraints."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Peer Review That Changed His Buying Habits",
            "when": "age 26",
            "event": "When shopping for a water purifier, Arjun ignored brand advertisements entirely and spent two weeks gathering opinions from colleagues and a close engineering friend before making his choice, which turned out to be significantly more reliable than what his manager had bought based on a sales pitch.",
            "lasting_impact": "This validated his distrust of institutional and commercial sources, making peer recommendations his primary and almost exclusive lens for evaluating any significant purchase or life decision."
          }
